  <h2 id="quick-install">Quick Install</h2>
  <p>For most users, the quick install is the easiest way to get started:</p>
  <pre><code>npx create-app@latest my-project</code></pre>
  <p>This command will:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Create a new project directory</li>
    <li>Install all necessary dependencies</li>
    <li>Set up default configuration</li>
    <li>Initialize a Git repository</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="manual-installation">Manual Installation</h2>
  <p>For more control over your setup, follow these manual installation steps:</p>

  <h3 id="clone-repository">Clone Repository</h3>
  <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/your-org/project.git
cd project</code></pre>

  <h3 id="install-dependencies">Install Dependencies</h3>
  <pre><code>npm install</code></pre>

  <h3 id="configure-environment">Configure Environment</h3>
  <p>Copy the example environment file and configure your settings:</p>
  <pre><code>cp .env.example .env</code></pre>
  <p>Then edit the <code>.env</code> file with your specific configuration values.</p>

  <h2 id="verify-installation">Verify Installation</h2>
  <p>After installation, verify everything is working correctly:</p>
  <pre><code>npm run dev</code></pre>
  <p>You should see output indicating the development server is running. Open your browser to <code>http://localhost:4321</code> to view your project.</p>

  <h2 id="troubleshooting">Troubleshooting</h2>
  <p>If you encounter issues during installation:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Permission errors:</strong> Try running with <code>sudo</code> or fix npm permissions</li>
    <li><strong>Node version mismatch:</strong> Use <code>nvm</code> to switch Node versions</li>
    <li><strong>Missing dependencies:</strong> Delete <code>node_modules</code> and run <code>npm install</code> again</li>
    <li><strong>Port conflicts:</strong> Check if another process is using port 4321</li>
  </ul>

  <blockquote>
    Still having issues? Check our <a href="/docs/guides">community guides</a> or open an issue on GitHub.
  </blockquote>
